
1. Install netcat

Type "apt-get install netcat-openbsd" as root to obtain compatible netcat.

2. Configure /etc/environment

The environment setting should be looked like the "environment" file.

3. Configure /etc/sudoers

Type "visudo" as root, add "env_keep" for proxy environemnts, please refer to the "sudoers" file.

4. Install socks-wrapper script

The script should be looked like the "socks-wrapper" file.

